steps.description:
Dry the flowers. Allow the flowers to dry for at least one week. See the wikiHow on how to dry herbs for the method to dry flowers. If you do not have access to your own violets, purchase dried, organic and unsprayed violets from a reputable store (such as a health food store). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/de/Make-Violet-Tea-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Violet-Tea-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/d/de/Make-Violet-Tea-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/aid182659-v4-728px-Make-Violet-Tea-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Store dried violet flowers in an opaque, airtight container. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/cf/Make-Violet-Tea-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Violet-Tea-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/c/cf/Make-Violet-Tea-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/aid182659-v4-728px-Make-Violet-Tea-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Make tea from the dried flowers. Add 1-2 teaspoons dried violets per cup of  boiling water. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/49/Make-Violet-Tea-Step-5Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Violet-Tea-Step-5Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/4/49/Make-Violet-Tea-Step-5Bullet3.jpg/aid182659-v4-728px-Make-Violet-Tea-Step-5Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
